'''累退稅'''（{{lang-en|regressive tax}}）是隨[[納稅人|納稅人]]收入和財富的增加而實際[[稅率|稅率]]逐步遞減的稅制。<ref>[http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/Regressive Webster] {{Wayback|url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/Regressive |date=20201111214921 }} (3): decreasing in rate as the base increases (a regressive tax)</ref><ref>[http://www.bartleby.com/61/71/R0127100.html American Heritage] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603151838/http://www.bartleby.com/61/71/R0127100.html |date=2008-06-03 }} (3). Decreasing proportionately as the amount taxed increases: a regressive tax.</ref><ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/regressive Dictionary.com] {{Wayback|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/regressive |date=20151222160536 }} (3).(of tax) decreasing proportionately with an increase in the tax base.</ref><ref>[http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1B1-376673.html Britannica Concise Encyclopedia] {{Wayback|url=http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1B1-376673.html |date=20090112150837 }}: Tax levied at a rate that decreases as its base increases.</ref><ref>Sommerfeld, Ray M., Silvia A. Madeo, Kenneth E. Anderson, Betty R. Jackson (1992), ''Concepts of Taxation'', Dryden Press: Fort Worth, TX</ref>

==例子==
[[銷售稅|銷售稅]]、[[增值稅|增值稅]]、[[燃油稅|燃油稅]]等基於[[日常開支|日常開支]]實際消耗而徵收的稅項多被認為是累退稅。雖然隨收入和財富增加，日常開支會隨之而上升，但這些衣、食、住、行的開支佔整體收入的比率，當收入達到一定金額之後，卻不升反跌。由於這稅率多為固定稅率，所以納稅人的實際稅率亦相對下跌。

